description:
&lt;p&gt;1x post: Band 7 Clinical Psychologist (or Family of) 1.0 wte full time, permanent post&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Clinical Psychologist who is a flexible team player and has a can do attitude to join and contribute to our thriving and innovative multi-disciplinary Tier 3 Adolescent Mental Health Team (AMHT) for the South of the county, based in Luton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team is part of wider and comprehensive Luton Specialist CAMH Service, offering a stepped model of mental health care. We are part of ELFT (East London Foundation Trust), which includes five CAMHS services across East London, Bedfordshire and Luton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary role of the team is to support adolescents and families experiencing complex and serious mental health problems. The AMHT delivers a robust multidisciplinary team approach offering individual, family and group interventions which are evidence based. There is also opportunity to develop unique services for the local population using a quality improvement approach. The post holders professional development will be well supported and actively encouraged by senior clinical psychology and Clinical Lead colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Luton is a fast growing hub and multi-ethnic community within a half hour train journey from central London, with the clinic a five-minute walk from the station. The Trust has an arrangement for 50% discount on season ticket fares with Thameslink, the rail provider, for its staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Luton CAMHS is a busy team working to four discrete child and adolescent mental health pathways: emotional &amp; behavioural difficulties in childhood and adolescence, neuro-developmental child &amp; adolescent care and with the CAMH Access Services offering early intervention through schools, GP practices and Early Help, delivers a stepped model of care. Luton (and ELFT) CAMHS is one of the ten national accelerator sites for piloting the new Thrive model for CAMHS and for the trailblazer Mental Health Support Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are welcomed from Clinical Psychologists, and others within the Family of Psychology, who want to make a significant contribution in our clinically led organisation, in a town whose multicultural demographic makes it an exciting and hugely fulfilling place to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome you to contact us or visit us for further information about our service:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Hilary Gahan, Associative Clinical Director and Medical Clinical Team Lead for AMHT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Sookraj, Non-medical Clinical Team Lead, AMHT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
